<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Overview">Overview</span></h2>
<p>An <a class="mw-selflink selflink">apartment tower</a> is a type of building. Apartment Towers are visible on the map as a 4x4 block of green lowercase 'a's, with a single uppercase 'A' denoting the garage door leading to the interior. Their layout consists of four separate towers walled off by concrete walls and a metal garage door which is usually closed, preventing access unless the player has aquired a <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Jackhammer" title="Jackhammer">Jackhammer</a>. The upper levels are accessible by four sets of staircases leading both up into the tower and down into the basement. While zombie-infested towers are most common, it is also possible for the player to encounter ones filled with NPCs, although currently (as of <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/0.D_(Danny)" title="0.D (Danny)">0.D (Danny)</a>), they are all Refugees with no quests or special dialogue. These towers can be a good source of NPC followers, however, as there are many refugees within.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Enemies">Enemies</span></h2>
<p>Apartment Towers spawn types of zombies commonly found in cities. While mainly normal <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Zombie" title="Zombie">zombies</a>, <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Zombie_child" title="Zombie child">zombie children</a> and <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Fat_zombie" title="Fat zombie">fat zombies</a>, the player should also expect a few <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Spitter_zombie" title="Spitter zombie">Spitters</a> and <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Smoker_zombie" title="Smoker zombie">Smokers</a>, an assortment of Military and Police zombies, and the possibility of one or two <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Shocker_zombie" title="Shocker zombie">Shocker Zombies</a> and/or <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Brute" class="mw-redirect" title="Brute">Brutes</a>, however later in the game some of the basic zombies might have <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Evolve&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Evolve (page does not exist)">evolved</a> into more advanced variants. In total, the player should expect upwards of sixty zombies scattered throughout the complex.
</p><p>If playing with wander spawns on, it is likely that the majority of the zombies will congregate on the ground floor, posing considerable threat to an unprepared survivor. A small number will have jumped out the upper-floor windows and fallen down outside the complex, usually around five on each corner. It is recommended a survivor planning to scavenge the area clear these zombies first, as they are normally fairly isolated and in small numbers.
</p><p>As the building is entirely concrete, judicious application of <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Explosives" title="Explosives">Explosives</a> or <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Fire" title="Fire">Molotov</a> is perfectly acceptable when dealing with the horde. A survivor confident in their melee skill may opt to place <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Nailboard_trap" title="Nailboard trap">nailboard traps</a> around the hole in the wall they used to enter, and lead zombies there to take them down one-by-one in the doorway, but beware of spitters turning the floor you're standing on to acid.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Loot">Loot</span></h2>
<p>Apartment Towers spawn standard house loot, which includes Basic Chemicals (Gallon jugs of <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Bleach" title="Bleach">Bleach</a> and <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Ammonia" title="Ammonia">Ammonia</a>) various common <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Comestibles/Food" title="Comestibles/Food">foodstuffs</a>, civilian <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Clothing" title="Clothing">Clothing</a>,, <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Alcohol" title="Alcohol">Alcohol</a>, and common <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Comestibles/Meds" title="Comestibles/Meds">Drugs</a> such as <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Antibiotic" title="Antibiotic">Antibiotics</a> or <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Codeine" title="Codeine">Codeine</a>. Skill Books seem to be rather rare, the majority spawned being novels and magazines.
Occasionally, apartments will generate with a room where a group of now-zombified soldiers made a last stand, which can be a small source of military-grade loot.
</p><p>The basement level contains a plethora of machinery which can be <span style="background-color: #F0F0F0; color: #333333; width: 2em; border: 1px outset #666; border-radius: .3em; -moz-border-radius: .3em; -webkit-border-radius: .3em; margin:0; padding:1px 2px; clear:none; font-family:monospace; font-size:1.2em">D</span>issassembled for various industrial scrap, lockers next to beds which may contain various hardware, and many rooms containing washing machines and clothes. 
</p><p>The roof of each tower spawns random trash (<a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Glass_jar" title="Glass jar">Glass Jars</a>, Empty <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Plastic_bottle" title="Plastic bottle">Plastic Bottles</a>, <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Newspaper_page" title="Newspaper page">Newspapers</a>) as well as two small rooms filled with more machinery and several lockers, which spawn Mechanic loot like small Engines and components.
</p>
